"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13826:\"<p>Are you looking for the best SMTP services for email marketing? </p>\n<p>An SMTP service helps you to send emails to your users and customers from your website safely, without fail.</p>\n<p>Emails are an important means of communication between your website and users.  So, it’s essential to ensure that your emails are properly sent and delivered to your users’ inbox. And, SMTP services help you achieve that goal. </p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll compare the six best SMTP services for email marketing in 2019.</p>\n<h3>What is SMTP? Why You Need an SMTP Service?</h4>\n<p>SMTP stands for Simple Mail Transfer Protocol. It is the industry standard for sending electronic messages or emails. It uses proper authentication, which increases the chances of your emails being delivered properly. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/smtpforemaildeliverability.png\" alt=\"SMTP Services for Email Deliverability\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217403\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/smtpforemaildeliverability.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/smtpforemaildeliverability-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;ve got a website, then you may have set up automated user-triggered emails to notify users about their activity on your site. For example, when they register a new account, change a password, order a product, purchase a product, etc. </p>\n<p>But a lot of times, your transactional emails like these may be failing to reach the users’ inbox. And, you may be losing lots of money because of the failure to communicate. </p>\n<p>The main reason behind this problem is that your mailing system is not configured correctly. For example, if you’re using WordPress, then the problem occurs because its default PHP mail() function is not configured correctly by most <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-hosting-services/\">hosting services</a>. </p>\n<p>So, the solution for this problem is to use an SMTP service which configures email authentication properly for you. For WordPress sites, you can use the most popular WordPress SMTP plugin <a href=\"https://wpmailsmtp.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WP Mail SMTP</a> and fix email deliverability. </p>\n<p>With that said, let’s take a look at the best SMTP services for reliable email marketing. </p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">1. Sendinblue</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sendinblueemailsoftware.png\" alt=\"SedninBlue Email Software\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-201597\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sendinblueemailsoftware.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/sendinblueemailsoftware-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sendinblue</a> is one of the most popular <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-email-newsletter-tools-compared-pros-and-cons/\">email marketing services</a> in the world. It offers SMTP email service for both user-triggered transactional emails and bulk email campaigns. Also, it provides a powerful SMS marketing and live chat solution for your business. </p>\n<p>Using Sendinblue, you can send transactional emails and highly targeted marketing emails to your users or subscribers. Backed by a team of email deliverability experts, it provides a reliable SMTP server for your business emails. </p>\n<p>Sendinblue works well with WordPress and other marketing tools like <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">OptinMonster</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-complete-beginners-guide-to-google-analytics-for-wordpress/\">Google Analytics</a>, and many more. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free plan with 300 emails per day. The starting paid plan Lite is available for $25 / month with 40,000 emails per month and no daily sending limits. </p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/mailjet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. Mailjet</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/mailjet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mailjet.png\" alt=\"Mailjet Best SMTP Service Provider\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217405\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mailjet.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mailjet-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/mailjet/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mailjet</a> is one of the best SMTP service providers available on the market. It comes with a robust and easy to use SMTP relay service that helps you send tons of emails to your users’ inbox. </p>\n<p>Mailjet offers a beginner-friendly email builder which lets you create beautiful emails easily in just a few clicks. Plus, it has advanced contact management tools to manage, segment, and grow your <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/why-collect-emails-benefits-of-building-an-email-list/\">email list</a>. </p>\n<p>Mailjet has built-in integration with WordPress, Magento, and other <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/which-is-the-best-website-platform-for-small-business/\">website platforms</a> so that you can use the SMTP email service easily on your site. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free plan with 6,000 emails per month (200 emails per day limit). The starting paid plan is available for $8.69 / month with 30,000 emails/month and no daily sending limit. </p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.mailgun.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Mailgun</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mailgun.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mailgun.png\" alt=\"Mailgun SMTP Relay Service\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217406\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mailgun.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/mailgun-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.mailgun.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mailgun</a> is a super powerful SMTP provider for developers. Its powerful email sending infrastructure lets you send millions of transactional and bulk emails with higher delivery rates. </p>\n<p>You can use Mailgun with a WordPress website easily. The popular SMTP plugin WP Mail SMTP also offers native integration with Mailgun to connect it to your WordPress site smoothly. </p>\n<p>Mailgun is a highly scalable SMTP service. However, it’s quite complicated for beginner-level users. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Mailgun offers pay-as-you-go pricing plans providing you the first 10,000 emails and 100 validations free every month. For 20,000 emails per month, you need to pay $5 / month. If you want a dedicated IP address, then you need to sign up with a Production plan which costs $79 / month. </p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://sendgrid.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. SendGrid</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://sendgrid.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/sendgrid.png\" alt=\"SendGrid Email SMTP Service\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217407\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/sendgrid.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/sendgrid-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://sendgrid.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SendGrid</a> is a popular email delivery service available on the market. It allows you to send email newsletters, promotions, shipping notifications, password resets, and all types of emails with confidence. </p>\n<p>SendGrid is user-friendly that you can easily integrate with their email API and send emails that will reach the inbox. Also, it lets you authenticate your domains and offers a dedicated IP address to boost email deliverability. </p>\n<p>It’s easy to integrate and use the SendGrid SMTP relay service with WordPress and other platforms. To connect your WordPress site with SendGrid, you can also use the WP Mail SMTP plugin free. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Free plan with 40,000 emails for 30 days and 100 emails per day. After that, their paid plans start from $24.95 /month.  </p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/ses/\" target=\"_blank\" re=\"nofollow\">5. Amazon SES</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/ses/\" target=\"_blank\" re=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazonses.png\" alt=\"Amazon SES Scalable SMTP provider\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217408\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazonses.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/amazonses-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/ses/\" target=\"_blank\" re=\"nofollow\">Amazon SES</a> or Amazon Simple Email Service is a highly scalable cloud-based email sending service. It’s a product of the leading cloud computing service company Amazon Web Services. </p>\n<p>The Amazon SES comes with a powerful SMTP interface capable of sending tons of emails smoothly. It includes features like content filtering, dedicated IP addresses, and reputation dashboard to improve your sender reputation. </p>\n<p>Hence you can confidently send transactional messages, marketing newsletters, and also receive the incoming emails. Its robust structure ensures that your emails don’t end up in spam folder. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: If you’re hosting your site on Amazon EC2, then you can send 62,000 emails/month for free. For other email clients and websites, you need to pay $0.10 every month for 1000 emails. </p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/gsuite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. G Suite</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/gsuite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gsuite.png\" alt=\"G Suite Google SMTP Service\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217409\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gsuite.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gsuite-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/gsuite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">G Suite</a> is a package of productivity apps for business by Google. It includes professional email, online storage, calendar, and more for your business. </p>\n<p>With G Suite, you can use Google’s SMTP servers to send emails to your customers. It’s easy to integrate the Gmail SMTP in WordPress with the WP Mail SMTP. </p>\n<p>However, it’s suitable only for small businesses because it lets you send only 2000 emails per day. </p>\n<p><strong>Pricing</strong>: Starts from $6 per user per month. </p>\n<h3>Connecting a SMTP Service to Your WordPress Site</h3>\n<p>Now that you know the best SMTP services on the market, you may be wondering how to connect an SMTP service with your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>If so, then you’re in luck! The best WordPress SMTP plugin <a href=\"https://wpmailsmtp.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WP Mail SMTP</a> makes it effortless to connect your WordPress site with the top SMTP relay services. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpmailsmtp.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpmailsmtp.png\" alt=\"WP Mail SMTP Best WordPress SMTP Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-217410\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpmailsmtp.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpmailsmtp-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WP Mail SMTP is available as a free plugin with easy setup options for Mailgun, SendGrid, Gmail SMTP, and more. There’s also the premium plan with Microsoft SMTP, Amazon SES SMTP support. </p>\n<p>Used by more than 1 million websites, WP Mail SMTP is the perfect SMTP solution for WordPress. To learn more, visit the <a href=\"https://wpmailsmtp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">official website</a> and <a href=\"https://wpmailsmtp.com/docs/\" target=\"_blank\">documentation</a>. </p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to find the best SMTP service for email marketing. You may also want to see our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-free-business-email-address/\">how to create a free business email address</a>.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful marketing and Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-smtp-services-for-email-marketing/\">6 Best SMTP Services for Email Marketing (Compared)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-smtp-services-for-email-marketing/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"What Is Gated Content and How to Use It to Get More Leads\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:191:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/what-is-gated-content-and-how-to-use-it-to-get-more-leads/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=what-is-gated-content-and-how-to-use-it-to-get-more-leads\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/what-is-gated-content-and-how-to-use-it-to-get-more-leads/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 22 Jul 2019 06:29:04 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=216729\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:603:\"<p>Looking for a way to generate more leads for your business? In the past, you might&#8217;ve been able to get away with a simple lead generation form. But fast forward to 2019 and the internet is more competitive than ever. If you want to gather the most leads possible, then you have to offer an [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/what-is-gated-content-and-how-to-use-it-to-get-more-leads/\">What Is Gated Content and How to Use It to Get More Leads</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"MonsterInsights Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13869:\"<p>Looking for a way to generate more leads for your business? </p>\n<p>In the past, you might&#8217;ve been able to get away with a simple lead generation form. But fast forward to 2019 and the internet is more competitive than ever. </p>\n<p>If you want to gather the most leads possible, then you have to offer an incentive in exchange. The technique is called content gating / gated content.  </p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll explain what gated content is and how to use it to get more leads.                                                          </p>\n<h3>What Is Gated Content? &#8211; A Simple Definition</h3>\n<p>Gated content is any online material that you lock behind a form. </p>\n<p>It can be a part of or an entire article online, a video, a report, an eBook, case study, or anything at all that requires your visitor to fill out a lead capture form before they can access it. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/gated-content-example-jeff-bullas.png\" alt=\"example of gated content from jeff bullas\" width=\"568\" height=\"286\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-207391\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/gated-content-example-jeff-bullas.png 568w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/gated-content-example-jeff-bullas-300x151.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\" /></p>\n<p>Gated content marketing is a great way to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/why-collect-emails-benefits-of-building-an-email-list/\">collect emails for your list</a>. As curious humans are, the gated content tempts your website visitors to complete the lead capture form.   </p>\n<p>With the gated content forms, you can ask for the email address and name only or in-depth information, including their interests. </p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve collected plenty of information, you can design marketing strategies to grow your business.  </p>\n<h3>3 Gated Content Examples and Ideas You Can Implement Today</h3>\n<p>So how can you get started with gated content for exponential lead growth? </p>\n<p>Let’s take a look at some different types and examples of gated content in action.</p>\n<p><strong>1. Content Locking: Perfect for High Authority Publications</strong></p>\n<p>You may have seen a few publications where part of, or the entire article is locked until signup. That is the article lock form of gated content in action.</p>\n<p>This one, for example, is from the Harvard Business Review.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/hbr-content-locking-min.png\" alt=\"HBR offers subscription based content\" width=\"568\" height=\"225\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-207598\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/hbr-content-locking-min.png 568w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/hbr-content-locking-min-300x119.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\" /></p>\n<p>It works because the articles are highly regarded, thanks to the publication’s reputation. </p>\n<p>This model may be used to generate leads for an ad-free subscription-based membership, and typically locks the content after a few posts have been viewed.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Lead Magnets: A Simple Way to Gather Leads</strong></p>\n<p>A lead magnet is a downloadable resource that you offer potential customers in exchange for their email address. Then you can educate them with <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/beginners-guide-to-email-marketing/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">email marketing</a> and convert them into buyers.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/lead-magnet-example.png\" alt=\"Lead magnet example\" width=\"560\" height=\"309\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-207618\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/lead-magnet-example.png 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/lead-magnet-example-300x166.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Here are some really good <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/9-lead-magnets-to-increase-subscribers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">lead magnet ideas</a> you could get started with today.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Content Upgrade: Build Your List With Targeted Subscribers</strong></p>\n<p>A content upgrade is a form of lead magnet created explicitly for a particular article. The information in a content upgrade usually adds even more value to a blog post.</p>\n<p>And here’s an example for a post talking about creating custom “Pin it” buttons.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/content-upgrade-example.png\" alt=\"content upgrades are a type of gated content\" width=\"560\" height=\"283\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-207601\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/content-upgrade-example.png 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/content-upgrade-example-300x152.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>This is a popular form of gated content because content upgrades are highly relevant to the post, so they tend to convert very well. In fact, ValueWalk, a popular financial and investment news site, saw a <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/case-study-how-valuewalk-increased-conversions-by-216-in-one-month-using-content-upgrades/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">216% increase in conversions</a> by offering content upgrades!</p>\n<p>To offer content upgrades, you will need to create standalone resources that add value to your post. Then, add an optin form to your post that will automatically deliver the content upgrade when the readers sign up.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/30-content-upgrade-ideas-to-grow-your-email-list/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Here are some content upgrade ideas</a> to get you started.</p>\n<h3>Does Gated Content Work? (Statistics and Case Studies)</h3>\n<p>Plainly, gated content works exceptionally well at converting leads. And not just any kind of leads, you’ll see higher quality leads too.</p>\n<p>Why is this so? </p>\n<p>Because only the people who are hyper interested in your content will convert.</p>\n<p>And as we’ll see shortly, gated content conversion rates can go as high as 45%! That’s 45 pre-qualified leads for every 100 visitors.</p>\n<p>Here are a few gated content case studies for your inspiration:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Photowebo <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-gated-content-increased-conversions-3806-percent/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">increased conversions 3806% </a>using gated content</li>\n<li>Whole Whale <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-this-marketing-agency-doubled-their-list-using-content-locking/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">converts 21.42% readers into subscribers</a> with content lock</li>\n<li>Trading Strategy Guides <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/content-locking-script-case-study/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">added 11,000 new subscribers</a> with content locking script (almost 7500 subscribers from a single piece of content) </li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optinmonster-tradingstrategies-contentlockingscript-stats.png\" alt=\"OptinMonster TradingStrategies Content Locking Script Stats\" width=\"620\" height=\"312\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216811\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optinmonster-tradingstrategies-contentlockingscript-stats.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optinmonster-tradingstrategies-contentlockingscript-stats-300x151.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Convinced to add gated content to your content marketing and lead generation plan? Here’s how to get started!</p>\n<h3>How to Gate Content For Lead Generation (Step by Step)</h3>\n<h4>Step 1: Creating High-value Content for Gating</h4>\n<p>To use gated content effectively without triggering negative impressions for your brand, it’s crucial to create high quality, high-value content for gating.</p>\n<p>In other words, you need to create gate worthy content.</p>\n<p>Some ideas include repurposing your best articles, offering a free webinar, and other downloadable resources. You can find lots of <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/9-lead-magnets-to-increase-subscribers/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">lead magnet ideas</a> in this post.</p>\n<p>And if you’ll be gating your article itself then just creating the article will do.</p>\n<h4>Step 2: Gating Your Content</h4>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve created premium content for gating, the next step is to lock your content. </p>\n<p>You can gate your content in many different ways. If you want to gate your article content, then you can simply add a content locker form in your article. </p>\n<p>If you are offering a downloadable lead magnet or content upgrade, then you can create <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-popup-plugins/\">email signup forms and popups</a>. </p>\n<p>Wondering how to add content blocking forms on your website? </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">OptinMonster</a> offers a complete solution for that! </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-bestpopupandleadgenerationtool.png\" alt=\"OptinMonster Best Popup and Lead Generation Tool\" width=\"620\" height=\"367\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-211601\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-bestpopupandleadgenerationtool.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/optinmonster-bestpopupandleadgenerationtool-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It’s the most powerful <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-lead-generation-plugins-for-wordpress/\">lead generation software</a> on the market. It allows you to create visually stunning and powerful email optin forms, content locking inline forms, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-a-countdown-timer-in-wordpress/\">countdown timers</a>, etc. easily on your website.</p>\n<p>You can OptinMonster to create gated content on WordPress as well as different other <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/which-is-the-best-website-platform-for-small-business/\">website platforms</a> and eCommerce sites.   </p>\n<p>Not only that, but it also lets you integrate your content gating forms with all the major <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-email-newsletter-tools-compared-pros-and-cons/\">email marketing services</a>. </p>\n<h4>Step 3: Track and Promote Your Gated Content</h4>\n<p>The final step is to promote your gated content and track your conversions.</p>\n<p>Thankfully, OptinMonster makes it easy to track your conversions! It has built-in integration for <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-complete-beginners-guide-to-google-analytics-for-wordpress/\">Google Analytics</a>, so you can easily connect your gated content forms with Google Analytics and see how they’re performing. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optinmonstergaintegration.png\" alt=\"Google Analytics Integration for OptinMonster\" width=\"620\" height=\"299\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216821\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optinmonstergaintegration.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/optinmonstergaintegration-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>So all you’ll have to worry about is promotion! To help you out, here’re some promotion tips:</p>\n<p><strong>1. Use a <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-landing-page-in-wordpress-step-by-step/\">landing page</a> where possible.</strong> Landing pages remove every distraction and help boost your conversion rate.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Use visuals to entice readers.</strong> People are becoming more and more visually oriented, so it’s going to take more than plain text to win them over. A mockup of the lead magnet is essential for success.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Link to your gated content frequently.</strong> Since very few people will promote with you, you must link to your content wherever there’s an opportunity to do so. Remember to use a visual too!</p>\n<p><strong>4. Consider paid promotion.</strong> For the same reason as the previous point, it may be wise to invest in paid promotion.</p>\n<p><strong>5. Consider adding a short promotional video to your landing page.</strong> Testimonials work great too!</p>\n<p><strong>6. Feature your gated content on your homepage.</strong> Your homepage will likely receive more visits than any other page on your website, so use up that real estate wisely. Link to your best-gated contents close to the top of the page with a Call to Action.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to understand what is gated content and how to use it to get more leads. You may also want to see our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/4-ways-to-boost-your-seo-rankings-with-google-analytics/\">4 ways to boost your SEO rankings with Google Analytics</a>. </p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful marketing and Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/what-is-gated-content-and-how-to-use-it-to-get-more-leads/\">What Is Gated Content and How to Use It to Get More Leads</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/what-is-gated-content-and-how-to-use-it-to-get-more-leads/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"Typeform Alternative for WordPress: WPForms vs Typeform\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:185:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/typeform-alternative-for-wordpress-wpforms-vs-typeform/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=typeform-alternative-for-wordpress-wpforms-vs-typeform\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:95:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/typeform-alternative-for-wordpress-wpforms-vs-typeform/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 18 Jul 2019 21:43:25 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Tools\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"tyepform for wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"typeform wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"tyform or wpforms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=216276\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:630:\"<p>Looking for the best plugin to add conversational forms on your WordPress site? Typeform and WPForms are the two most popular form builders on the market. Both of them allow you to create beautiful interactive forms and surveys on your website. But which one is better? In this article, we’ll compare WPforms vs Typeform side [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/typeform-alternative-for-wordpress-wpforms-vs-typeform/\">Typeform Alternative for WordPress: WPForms vs Typeform</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18487:\"<p>Looking for the best plugin to add conversational forms on your WordPress site? </p>\n<p>Typeform and WPForms are the two most popular form builders on the market. Both of them allow you to create beautiful interactive forms and surveys on your website. But which one is better? </p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll compare WPforms vs Typeform side by side to help you choose the best form builder plugin for your needs. </p>\n<h3>Typeform vs WPForms: Table of Contents</h3>\n<p>The main points of comparison between Typeform vs WPForms are given below in the table of contents. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#overview\">Overview</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#easeofuse\">Ease of Use</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#features\">Features</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#pricing\">Pricing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#support\">Support</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#conclusion\">Conclusion: WPForms vs Typeform</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Now let’s take a look at these factors in more details. </p>\n<h3 id=\"overview\">Overview</h3>\n<p>Typeform and WPForms both are powerful form builders. However, the way they work is mostly different. Let’s get started with the general overview of both these platforms. </p>\n<h4>Typeform</h4>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeform.png\" alt=\"Typeform Conversational Form Builder\" width=\"620\" height=\"366\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216290\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeform.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeform-300x177.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Typeform is one of the most popular form builders on the market. It’s a standalone SaaS (Software as a Service) software which allows you to build forms and add them to your website. </p>\n<p>With Typeform, you can create beautiful conversational forms easily and engage your audience. Unlike regular forms, they show just one question at a time that excites users to complete the form. </p>\n<p>The interactive forms are great for contact forms, surveys, quizzes, shopping cart forms, customer feedback forms, etc. They’re proven to reduce form abandonment and collect more data. </p>\n<h4>WPForms</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms.png\" alt=\"WPForms Best Form Builder Plugin for WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"412\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216291\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpforms-300x199.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a> is the most user-friendly WordPress form plugin on the market. Unlike Typeform, it’s a WordPress plugin which lets you create forms right inside your WordPress dashboard. </p>\n<p>Using WPForms, you can create simple contact forms as well as advanced forms like surveys, polls, quizzes, order forms, etc. on your WordPress site easily. And, the best part is that you can turn each form into a conversational form with just a few clicks. </p>\n<p>WPForms offers a simple drag and drop form builder interface for building forms. No coding is required. </p>\n<p>Undoubtedly, WPForms is the best Typeform alternative for WordPress. </p>\n<h3 id=\"easeofuse\">Ease of use</h3>\n<p>Ease of use is the most important factor to consider when choosing a form plugin. You need an easy to use form solution because it allows you to build forms quickly and save time for other more productive tasks. </p>\n<h4>Typeform</h4>\n<p>Creating forms in Typeform is fairly straightforward. It comes with more than 60 templates to get you started quickly. You can choose one of them or start from scratch. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformtemplates.png\" alt=\"Typeform Templates\" width=\"620\" height=\"466\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216292\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformtemplates.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformtemplates-300x225.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Customizing the Typeform templates is also easy. You can edit the questions, add new questions, add login smart jump to your questions,  etc. easily. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/editingatypeform.png\" alt=\"Editing a Typeform\" width=\"620\" height=\"377\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216293\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/editingatypeform.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/editingatypeform-300x182.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Making forms in Typeform is pretty simple; however, adding the forms to your WordPress site is a bit tricky. You need to find an embed code and add that to your website on every page where you want to display the form. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformembedcode.png\" alt=\"Typeform Embed Code\" width=\"620\" height=\"412\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216294\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformembedcode.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformembedcode-300x199.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>If you’re not familiar with HTML codes, then it’ll be a quite confusing task for you. </p>\n<p>Another disadvantage is that you need to visit the Typeform website every time you want to create a form or get a code. </p>\n<p>If you’re looking for a quick and simple way to add forms in WordPress, then WPForms is the better option. </p>\n<h4>WPForms</h4>\n<p>WPForms makes it super easy to create forms in WordPress. There’re tons of pre-designed templates to let you get started quickly. By default, there’re a handful of templates, and you can add 100 more templates with the Form Templates Pack addon. </p>\n<p>You can choose one of the form templates or start a new one from scratch. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformstemplates.png\" alt=\"WPForms Templates\" width=\"620\" height=\"419\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216295\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformstemplates.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformstemplates-300x203.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Creating and customizing forms in WPForms is super easy. It offers beginner-friendly drag and drop form builder, which lets you quickly add fields, customize, and make a form. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformsdragandropformeditor.png\" alt=\"WPForms Drag and Drop Form Editor\" width=\"620\" height=\"454\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216307\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformsdragandropformeditor.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformsdragandropformeditor-300x220.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you’ve built a form, you can quickly transform that into a conversational form with just a few clicks. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableconversationalforms.png\" alt=\"Enable Conversational Forms in WPForms\" width=\"620\" height=\"291\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216308\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableconversationalforms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableconversationalforms-300x141.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>And, when your conversational form is ready, you can easily embed it on your posts and pages. It offers a native block which lets you add your forms anywhere on your WordPress site easily. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/addformstoyourwordpressposts.png\" alt=\"Adding WPForms to Your WordPress Posts\" width=\"620\" height=\"380\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216309\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/addformstoyourwordpressposts.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/addformstoyourwordpressposts-300x184.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>It’s the benefit of using a native WordPress plugin over a SaaS software like Typeform. While Typeform requires you to paste an embed code to your page, WPforms makes it simple with its native block. </p>\n<h3 id=\"features\">Features</h3>\n<p>Now that you know both Typeform and WPForms allow you to create conversational forms, you may want to know what more features they offer. Let’s take a look at the features they offer to help you grow your website. </p>\n<h4>Typeform</h4>\n<p>Typeform mainly focuses on creating conversational forms; hence, it offers some cool features to make your forms more interactive and human. </p>\n<p>For example, it provides a smart jump feature which shows different questions based on the users’ answer to the previous questions.  This feature helps to make your forms more personal and humane. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformlogicjump.png\" alt=\"Typeform Logic Jump\" width=\"620\" height=\"296\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216310\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformlogicjump.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformlogicjump-300x143.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Typeform lets you integrate your forms with plenty of third-party services and tools. You can integrate with popular email marketing tools like MailChimp, Constant Contact, Drip, ActiveCampaign, and more. </p>\n<p>Similarly, you can connect your forms with analytics, support, lead generation, and more tools. </p>\n<h4>WPForms</h4>\n<p>WPForms offers some exclusive features that make it the best choice for WordPress forms. It includes powerful addons to extend its features and functionalities. </p>\n<p>The Signature addon allows your users to sign your forms electronically. It’s useful for signing contracts and agreements. </p>\n<p>For payments, it includes addons for PayPal and Stripe. You can create order forms, donation forms, and collect payments. </p>\n<p>WPForms has smooth integration with the major email marketing services, including AWeber, Campaign Monitor, Drip, GetResponse, and MailChimp. </p>\n<p>Best of all, it provides an exclusive Form Abandonment addon to help you recover leads from the abandoned forms. The addon saves partial entries and lets you follow up with the interested prospects. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms.png\" alt=\"Enable Form Abandonment Lead Capture in WPForms\" width=\"620\" height=\"278\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213110\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>With all these amazing features, WPForms is an excellent form builder plugin for WordPress. </p>\n<h3 id=\"pricing\">Pricing</h3>\n<p>Choosing the best-priced plugin allows you to save money for more critical growth tools. Let’s take a look at the pricing plans of WPForms vs Typeform.</p>\n<h4>Typeform</h4>\n<p>Typeform offers mainly 3 different pricing plans: Basic, Pro, and Pro+. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformpricing.png\" alt=\"Typeform Pricing\" width=\"620\" height=\"328\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216312\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformpricing.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformpricing-300x159.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The Basic plan is free; however, it has minimal features. You can get only 100 responses per month and add only 10 questions per Typeform.  And, it supports only the basic question types.</p>\n<p>The Pro plan is available for $30 / month or $350 / year. It supports unlimited responses, unlimited questions, and advanced question types as well. Plus, it has more powerful features like Logic Jump, Calculator, Custom Thank You Screen, and more. </p>\n<p>The most expensive Typeform plan is Pro+ which is available for $59 / month or $700 / year. It lets you use analytics tools like Google Tag Manager, the Facebook pixel with your forms. And, it also enables you to remove Typeform branding from your forms. </p>\n<p>The Typeform pricing seems quite expensive for the small businesses which are on a budget. </p>\n<h4>WPForms</h4>\n<p> In comparison to the Typeform, WPForms offers advanced features at a much lower price. It has mainly four pricing plans: Basic, Plus, Pro, and Elite. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformspricing.png\" alt=\"WPForms Pricing\" width=\"620\" height=\"556\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216313\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformspricing.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformspricing-300x269.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The Basic plan costs you only $39.50 / year, and it lets you create unlimited forms and accept unlimited entries. It supports advanced fields, file uploads, conditional logic, etc. With this plan, you can also connect your forms with Constant Contact and collect emails for campaigns. </p>\n<p>The Plus plan is available for $99.50 / year and lets you connect more email marketing tools. It also allows you to create newsletter forms. </p>\n<p>The Pro plan is the best WPForms deal that comes with all the powerful features of the plugin. It includes PayPal and Stripe addons to accept payments. It’s available for $199.50 / year. </p>\n<p>The highest WPForms plan costs $299.50 / year. It comes with WordPress multisite support.</p>\n<p>WPForms also offers a free version to the users looking for simple contact forms. </p>\n<p>The cost comparison clearly shows that WPForms offers more affordable forms. If you think Typeform is expensive for you, WPForms is the best alternative available for you. </p>\n<h3 id=\"support\">Support</h3>\n<p>Customer support is another crucial thing to consider. You need a very dedicated and expert support provider that can help you right when you need it.  </p>\n<h4>Typeform</h4>\n<p>Typeform website offers a help center with extensive documentation. You can find tutorials on how to create a form, connect with different tools, how to share your forms, and more. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformhelpcenter.png\" alt=\"Typeform Help Center\" width=\"620\" height=\"385\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216314\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformhelpcenter.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/typeformhelpcenter-300x186.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Besides that, you can contact the customer support via the support form; however, it’s limited. </p>\n<h4>WPForms</h4>\n<p>Customer support at WPForms is excellent. They offer instant technical support via support tickets. </p>\n<p>The WPForms website also includes a documentation hub with dozens of articles on how to use the plugin. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformsdocumentation.png\" alt=\"WPForms Documentation\" width=\"620\" height=\"385\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-216315\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformsdocumentation.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wpformsdocumentation-300x186.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Besides, you can visit their blog for useful articles, tips, and tutorials. The free version users can simply post questions in the plugin support forum page on WordPress.org website. </p>\n<h3 id=\"conclusion\">Conclusion: Which is Better?</h3>\n<p>After reviewing the two form builders Typeform and WPForms, we conclude that WPForms is the clear winner for WordPress forms. It allows you to create any form easily in WordPress, whereas there’s some learning curve to add Typeform forms in WordPress. </p>\n<p>Another benefit of using WPForms is that you get all the features at a much lower price. With the WPForms Pro plan that costs $199.50 / year, you can create conversational forms and use most of its powerful features. </p>\n<p>Whereas the Typeform Pro costs $350 / year for fewer features. You need to buy their most expensive plan Pro+ for $700 / year to remove the Typeform branding. </p>\n<p>Last but not least, WPForms is a WordPress plugin, whereas Typeform is not. WPForms is built the WordPress way. And, it lets you create forms and configure everything right from your dashboard. But you need to visit Typeform website whenever you need to add, edit your forms. </p>\n<p>WPForms is the best form builder for WordPress sites. And, the perfect Typeform alternative for WordPress. </p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to find out the differences between WPForms vs Typeform and decide which tool to use on your WordPress site. You may also want to see our guide on how to <a href=https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-your-wordpress-form-conversions-in-google-analytics/>track your WordPress form conversions with Google Analytics</a>.  </p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/typeform-alternative-for-wordpress-wpforms-vs-typeform/\">Typeform Alternative for WordPress: WPForms vs Typeform</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/typeform-alternative-for-wordpress-wpforms-vs-typeform/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"Which Is the Best Website Platform for Small Business? (2019)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:183:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/which-is-the-best-website-platform-for-small-business/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=which-is-the-best-web