;s:11:\"forms addon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"tracking form abandonment\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"wordpress forms tracking\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=213080\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:608:\"<p>Do you want to track form abandonment on your WordPress site? As forms are major points of interaction on a website, tracking form abandonment on your site lets you know how well users are engaged with your forms and other content. In this article, we’ll show you how to easily track form abandonment in WordPress [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress/\">How to Track Form Abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12408:\"<p>Do you want to track form abandonment on your WordPress site? </p>\n<p>As forms are major points of interaction on a website, tracking form abandonment on your site lets you know how well users are engaged with your forms and other content. </p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to easily track form abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way). </p>\n<h3>Tracking Form Abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-complete-beginners-guide-to-google-analytics-for-wordpress/\">Google Analytics</a> is the most widely used web analytics tool for tracking website traffic, conversions, and more. </p>\n<p>It lets you track a wide variety of metrics including <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-ecommerce-sales-in-google-analytics/\">eCommerce transactions</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-your-wordpress-form-conversions-in-google-analytics/\">form conversions</a>, form abandonment, and more, however using it is a bit tricky. </p>\n<p>If you’re a beginner, then you’ll need to invest lots of your time to understand <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-does-google-analytics-work-beginners-guide/\">how Google Analytics works</a>. Not only that you also need to spend money to hire a developer for configuring advanced metrics. </p>\n<p>But thankfully, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> plugin makes it super easy for WordPress users. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/monsterinsightsbestgapluginforwordpress.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Best Google Analytics Plugin for WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"320\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-186638\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/monsterinsightsbestgapluginforwordpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/monsterinsightsbestgapluginforwordpress-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It lets you configure form abandonment tracking and other important metrics in WordPress with just a few steps. </p>\n<p>To get started, you need to install and activate the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights plugin</a> and then connect it with your Google Analytics account. For detailed instructions, see our step by step guide on how to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">install Google Analytics in WordPress with MonsterInsights</a>. </p>\n<p>After that, you need to install the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/forms/\">MonsterInsights Forms addon</a> for tracking your forms. Go to <strong>MonsterInsights &raquo; Addons</strong> page from your dashboard and then install the Forms addon. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installmiformsaddon.png\" alt=\"Install MonsterInsights Forms Addon\" width=\"620\" height=\"168\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213104\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installmiformsaddon.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installmiformsaddon-300x81.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s all! Now MonsterInsights will automatically start tracking your WordPress forms. </p>\n<p>If you want to reconfirm that, then you need to visit the <strong>MonsterInsights &raquo; Settings</strong> page and click on the Conversions tab. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/miformstrackingsettings.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Forms Tracking Settings\" width=\"620\" height=\"406\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213105\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/miformstrackingsettings.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/miformstrackingsettings-300x196.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As shown in the screenshot above, the plugin will automatically detect your form plugin, and enable forms tracking. It supports all the major <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/\">WordPress form plugins</a> like <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a>, <a href=\"https://formidableforms.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Formidable Forms</a>, and more. </p>\n<p>After that, you may need to wait sometime to view your reports. It can take a few hours to 48 hours for Google Analytics to collect fresh data. </p>\n<h3>Viewing Your WordPress Form Tracking Stats</h3>\n<p>You can view your WordPress form tracking reports by going to <strong>MonsterInsights &raquo; Reports &raquo; Forms</strong> from your dashboard. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsightsformsreport.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Forms Tracking Reports\" width=\"620\" height=\"406\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213106\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsightsformsreport.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/monsterinsightsformsreport-300x196.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The MonsterInsights Forms report shows the total number of impressions, conversions, and conversion rate for each WordPress form. </p>\n<p>Now you can easily find out the number of people who abandoned your form. Wouldn’t it be great if more people who viewed your form fill it out?</p>\n<p>You can view this report also in your Google Analytics account. Simply click on the ‘View Full Forms Report’ button in your MonsterInsights forms report, and it will redirect you to the top events page in Google Analytics. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gatopevents-wpformsreports.png\" alt=\"Google Analytics Top Events Report - Forms Conversions\" width=\"620\" height=\"327\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213107\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gatopevents-wpformsreports.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/gatopevents-wpformsreports-300x158.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As Google Analytics treats forms related actions as events, forms tracking reports are shown under the Events category. </p>\n<p>By default, you can see the stats for event action. You can click on the ‘Event Label’ link to see the performance of your individual forms. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eventlabelgatopevents.png\" alt=\"View Event Label for Google Analytics Events\" width=\"620\" height=\"275\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213108\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eventlabelgatopevents.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/eventlabelgatopevents-300x133.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3>Recovering the Leads from the Abandoned Forms Using WPForms</h3>\n<p>Form abandonment is the real problem that you will miss your potential leads/ customers at the last point. But <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a> users can now solve that problem and turn those abandoning users into loyal customers. </p>\n<p>WPForms is the most user-friendly as well as the most powerful WordPress form plugin in the market. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms-wordpress-form-builder-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"WPForms Best WordPress Form Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-158461\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms-wordpress-form-builder-plugin.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms-wordpress-form-builder-plugin-300x121.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>It allows you to easily <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form-in-wordpress-the-simple-way/\">create simple contact forms</a> to advanced forms like <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-survey-in-wordpress/\">surveys</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-an-order-form-in-wordpress-the-easy-way/\">order forms</a>, multi-page forms, and more in your WordPress blog. </p>\n<p>WPForms comes with an exclusive <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-abandonment-addon/\" target=\"_blank\">Form Abandonment addon</a> to help you recover leads from the abandoned forms. The addon saves partial entries and lets you follow up with the interested prospects. </p>\n<p>This feature is especially useful for support request forms, order forms, request quote forms, etc. For any reason, the users may have abandoned your form, but you can follow up and build new relationships with them. </p>\n<p>To use the addon, go to <strong>WPForms &raquo; Addons</strong> page and then install the Form Abandonment Addon. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installformabandonmentaddonwpforms.png\" alt=\"Install Form Abandonment Addon WPForms Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"191\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213109\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installformabandonmentaddonwpforms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/installformabandonmentaddonwpforms-300x92.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, you need to enable this option in your WordPress forms. If you’ve existing forms, then you need to edit them and enable this option. </p>\n<p>For example, we’ll edit Billing / Order Form in our demo website. </p>\n<p>In your form editor screen, click on the ‘Settings’ menu. After that, click the ‘Form Abandonment’ option and check the box next to ‘Enable form abandonment lead capture.’ </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms.png\" alt=\"Enable Form Abandonment Lead Capture in WPForms\" width=\"620\" height=\"278\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213110\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/enableformabandonmentleadcapturewpforms-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s all! Now WPForms will record the entries for the abandoned forms and lets you optimize them. </p>\n<p>Like all the other entries, you can find the abandoned form entries as well in the Entries menu. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms.png\" alt=\"Entry Status of Abandoned and Completed Forms\" width=\"518\" height=\"410\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-213111\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms.png 518w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms-300x237.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 518px) 100vw, 518px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you can contact these users and offer them the products they may be interested in. </p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to learn how to track form abandonment in WordPress – the easy way. And also to learn to how to recover leads from the abandoned forms using WPForms. </p>\n<p>You may also want to see our step by step guide on how to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-google-analytics-to-amp-pages-on-wordpress/\">track your AMP traffic using Google Analytics</a>. </p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress/\">How to Track Form Abandonment in WordPress (The Easy Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-form-abandonment-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"35+ Best WordPress Plugins 2019 (Grow Your Website FASTER!)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:169:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-marketers/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=best-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-marketers\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-marketers/#respond\";s: